16/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry has opened a portion of its archive to the public, according to Ivan Komitski, the head of the ministry's Information and Archive Directorate. He said the action was in line with the law on classified information. The documents date from 1946-1964 and exclude any personal files. Documents from the former Communist-era State Security, covering 1978-1990, would be opened to the public at a later date. (Monitor - 16/05/06; Mediapool - 15/05/06)
